{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"85678690-cec4-4c86-892b-03dcdddd9999","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='({0}pt)'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding the `xmlns:vm` namespace and the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. All existing `{Binding …}` expressions stay the same — the XAML compiler now resolves them at build time instead of via reflection at runtime.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**2. Enable strict mode in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat invalid compiled bindings as build errors, not warnings -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this in place:\n\n| Scenario | What happens |\n|---|---|\n| `{Binding Themee}` (typo) | **CS error** — property not found on `SettingsViewModel` |\n| `{Binding FontSize}` bound to a `string` control property | **CS error** — type mismatch |\n| Missing `x:DataType` on a page | **CS warning** (error with strict mode) |\n\n**3. Key rules to remember:**\n\n- `x:DataType` can be set on **any element** and is inherited by children — useful when a `DataTemplate` binds to a different type.\n- To opt out for a single binding (e.g., binding to `BindingContext` itself), use `x:DataType=\"\"` or the **escape hatch** `{Binding Source={RelativeSource Self}, Path=…}`.\n- Compiled bindings also give a **measurable perf boost** — they skip `Reflection.Emit` / `SetValue` overhead at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10d88b27-6bfd-4500-a429-be7f5f6a9384","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there are no existing files. The user is asking me to show them how to convert a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. Let me provide a clear example and explanation.","outputTokens":802,"requestId":"A42D:3B9434:5DB7876:662B2DA:69F0042B"},"id":"16c99d44-0467-40fa-b9fa-1a39c44c988c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:50:03.951Z","parentId":"018c7b44-6562-4e58-910e-ae3ce8a4d291"}
